<isis lang="en">
    <stitle>ELECTRICAL SYSTEM TROUBLESHOOTING GUIDE - 2000, 4000, 8000 - ELECTRONIC ENGINES, CUMMINS M11E AND N14E -
        TROUBLESHOOTING - Vehicle Speed Sensor
    </stitle>
    <svcman/>
    <svcproc svcproctype="troubleshoot" graphiccount="0">
        <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
        <svcprocinfo>
            <para>When monitoring engine functions with a DDR and the vehicle is moving the miles-per-hour will display
                as MPH=XXX (actual vehicle speed if operating properly). To test the sensor and circuits to the ECM, use
                the following diagnostic steps.
            </para>
        </svcprocinfo>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS)</title>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">Disconnect engine harness connector (325) from the sensor. Loosen the locknut and remove
                    the sensor. The harness connector and sensor should be free of damage or corrosion. Remove any metal
                    shavings or debris from the sensor.
                </para>
            </step1>
            <step1>
                <para count="1">To install the sensor, turn in until the sensor contacts the transmission speedometer
                    gear, then back out
                    <emph type="bold">one full turn.</emph>
                    Tighten locknut to 34-37 Nm (25-35 ft-lbs). This assures that the sensor is adjusted properly for
                    the next test.
                </para>
            </step1>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
            <specpara>
                <warning>
                    <para>For Step 5, use AC voltmeter with sufficient length leads to avoid personal contact with
                        rotating vehicle wheels during test.
                    </para>
                </warning>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0823523" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.76in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.80in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.53in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Inspect VSS for damage and proper adjustment before performing this test. Refer to
                                    Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor (VSS) above.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Repair, adjust or replace vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Disconnect engine harness (325) from VSS and use test leads to measure resistance
                                    between terminal A and B of sensor connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, term. A to B.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>600 to 800 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Measure resistance to ground at both sensor terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, term. A and B to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the vehicle speed sensor (VSS).</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Block front wheels and place rear axles on floor stands.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Connect meter leads to test leads.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Run engine at idle speed, with transmission in high gear. Measure voltage across
                                    the two sensor terminals.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS, across terminals.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>2.0 volts AC.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>VSS checks good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace the VSS (refer to Inspecting and Adjusting the Vehicle Speed Sensor [VSS]
                                    above).
                                    <emph type="bold">NOTE: Improper sensor adjustment will cause low, erratic or no
                                        output.
                                    </emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
        <svcsubproc>
            <title>Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuits To ECM</title>
            <para>To check circuits between the ECM and the speedometer/tachometer unit, refer to
                <hotlnk document="s08230_107.xml" xrefid="x0823522">ATA Data Link Connector (313) and
                    Speedometer/Tachometer Input Circuits</hotlnk>.
            </para>
            <specpara>
                <caution>
                    <para>When testing at ECM connector (320), do not use probes or leads other than Cummins test leads,
                        Part No. 3822758. The connector will be damaged. The leads must fit snug without expanding the
                        connector terminal.
                    </para>
                </caution>
            </specpara>
            <table id="t0823524" tblwidth="full-page" frame="all" numbered="no" view="reveal">
                <title>Testing Vehicle Speed Sensor Circuits To ECM</title>
                <tgroup cols="7" colsep="1" rowsep="1" align="center" charoff="50">
                    <colspec colname="1" charoff="50" colwidth="0.59in"/>
                    <colspec colname="2" charoff="50" colwidth="0.50in"/>
                    <colspec colname="3" charoff="50" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                    <colspec colname="4" charoff="50" colwidth="0.85in"/>
                    <colspec colname="5" charoff="50" colwidth="0.75in"/>
                    <colspec colname="6" charoff="50" colwidth="0.69in"/>
                    <colspec colname="7" charoff="50" colwidth="1.65in"/>
                    <thead>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">STEP</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">KEY</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">ACTION</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">TEST POINTS</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">YES-IN SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>
                                    <emph type="bold">NO-OUT OF SPEC.</emph>
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </thead>
                    <tbody valign="top">
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>1.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Remove conn. (325) from vehicle speed sensor. Remove ECM conn. (320) from the ECM
                                    and inspect (refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s08230_100.xml" xrefid="x0823510">Inspecting International Engine
                                        Harness ECM Connector (320)</hotlnk>. ECM harness connector and ECM pins OK?
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Replace harness conn. terminals if damaged. If ECM pins are damaged, have Cummins
                                    dealer replace ECM. Refer to
                                    <hotlnk document="s08230_102.xml" xrefid="x0823511">Accelerator/ ECM Calibration
                                    </hotlnk>
                                    to recalibrate ECM/ accelerator pedal.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>2.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (320), use test leads and measure resistance to gnd. at terminals 3
                                    and 7 .
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(320), term. 3 and 7 to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short to ground in circuit with 100K ohms or less, then repair.</para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>3.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (320), measure resistance between terminals 3 and 7 and all other
                                    terminals in connector.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(320), term. 3 and 7 and all others.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>>100K ohms</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate short circuit between circuits where resistance between terminals is 100K
                                    ohms or less, then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>4.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>On</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At conn. (320) use test leads and jumper terminal 3 to ground. At conn. (325)
                                    measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AJ.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(325), 97AJ to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AJ between connectors (320) and (325),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>5.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>At connector (320) use test leads and jumper terminal 7 to ground. At conn. (325)
                                    measure resistance to ground at circuit 97AK.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>(325), 97AK to gnd.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>&#60;5 ohms.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Go to next step.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>Locate open or poor connection in circuit 97AK between connectors (320) and (325),
                                    then repair.
                                </para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                        <row>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>6.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para>Off</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry>
                                <para>The vehicle speed sensor circuits between the sensor and ECM check good.</para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                            <entry align="center">
                                <para></para>
                            </entry>
                        </row>
                    </tbody>
                </tgroup>
            </table>
        </svcsubproc>
    </svcproc>
